Usually black american swifts build nests at a height of 0.4 to 6 m, and the angle of inclination of the surface can reach 45 ° [20]. 20 mm [2]. Other sources indicate sizes up to 200 mm along the rock [27]. The internal dimensions of nests in British Columbia are 85 × 70 mm, in California and Montana - a diameter of 90-91 mm [20]. The size and shape of the nest depend on the size of the niche, as well as on the age of the nest [27].